body: "GitHub: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/438\n\n## Problem\nNo way to create/update an item from one JSON document: `pm create -` treats `-` as the title; `--stdin` is unknown. Structured agents must translate an item into 10-20 flags; strict-mode errors suggest a 19-flag retry.\n\n## Proposed fix\n`pm create --stdin-json` and `pm update <id> --stdin-json` accepting the same item shape `pm get --json` emits (round-trip: get | modify | update). Flags win over document keys when both given. Reject unknown keys with did-you-mean.\n\n## Definition of done\nCreate+update accept full item documents on stdin incl. deps/comments/files facets; round-trip spec (get -> update) green; SDK/MCP parity noted (MCP already takes structured params); docs + contracts updated."
